did.unittitle: A. Lee McAlester Archives

repository.corpname: Yale Peabody Museum of Natural History

did.abstract: The archives of A. Lee McAlester including mostly maps and photographs encompassing his career at Yale. These focus on his 1960 Yale dissertation, "Pelecypod faunas of the Late Devonian Chemung Stage, central New York."

prefercite.head: Cite As
prefercite.p: A. Lee McAlester Archives, Invertebrate Paleontology, Yale Peabody Museum

bioghist.head: Biographical Sketch
bioghist.p: Curater for Division of Inververtabrate Paleontology at the Yale Peabody Museum. 1959-1975. PhD from Yale University in 1960.

scopecontent.head: Description of the Material
scopecontent.p: Includes maps from his field areas, photographs of specimens, and miscellaneous other material (including his 1957 both biographic and collections related).
